org.jcvi.jillion.assembly.tigr.tasm

Interface TasmContig

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Contig<TasmAssembledRead>

    public interface TasmContig
extends Contig<TasmAssembledRead>
    TasmContig is a Contig that contains extra metadata attributes specific to the TigrAssembler format.
    Author:
    dkatzel

    • Method Detail

      • getSampleId

        Integer getSampleId()
        Get the TIGR Project Database Sample Id for this contig (legacy TIGR systems often referred to this value as the bac id). It is possible for multiple contigs to have the same sample id if the sample is in many pieces.
        Returns:
        null if this contig doesn't have a sample id; or a non-null integer value if it does.

      • getCeleraAssemblerId

        Long getCeleraAssemblerId()
        Get GUID that this contig was assigned by the Celera Assembler.
        Returns:
        null if this contig doesn't have a Celera Assembler Id; or a non-null Long value if it does.

      • getTigrProjectAssemblyId

        Long getTigrProjectAssemblyId()
        Get the TIGR Project Database assembly Id for for this contig. (legacy TIGR systems often referred to this value as the asmbl_id). This value should be unique across the sample sample id.
        Returns:
        null if this contig doesn't have a asmbl_id; or a non-null integer value if it does.

      • getAssemblyMethod

        String getAssemblyMethod()
        Get the method used to create this contig. This value is often the name of the assembler used or the software program that generated this contig.
        Returns:
        a String description of what software created this contig; or null if no such information is provided.

      • getComment

        String getComment()
        Comment explaining what this contig is which might include the name of the chromosome or segment this contig belongs.
        Returns:
        a String; may be null if no comment exists.

      • getCommonName

        String getCommonName()
        Common name for this contig. Often this value is a combination of the comment and sample id.
        Returns:
        a String; may be null if no common name exists.

      • getEditPerson

        String getEditPerson()
        Get the username of the last person who edited this contig.
        Returns:
        null if no edit information is available; or the user name as a string.
        See Also:
        getEditDate()

      • getEditDate

        Date getEditDate()
        The date of the last edit to this contig.
        Returns:
        the Date when this contig was last edited; or null if no edit information is available.
        See Also:
        getEditPerson()

      • isCircular

        boolean isCircular()
        Is this contig circular.
        Returns:
        true if this contig is circulr; false if linear. Defaults to false.

      • getAvgCoverage

        double getAvgCoverage()
        Get the average ungapped read coverage as a double.
        Returns:
        the coverage will always by ≥ 0.

      • isAnnotationContig

        boolean isAnnotationContig()
        Is this contig a TIGR "annotation" contig. An annotation contig has information such as average coveage and number of reads set to non-zero values, but does not actually contain the underlying reads. It is essentially only the consensus plus meta data.
        Returns:
        true if this contig is an annotation contig; false otherwise.
